              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Pulsed beams of less than 1 ns FWHM"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The thicknesses of target and 12C backing are",
                "        Target(ug/cm**2)   Backing(ug/cm**2)",
                "  SM-148       30                40",
                "  BA-136       40                12",
                "  SN-124       17                12",
                "The target was located 18 cm away from the central",
                "cathode foil of each MWPC."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The CUBE spectrometer consisting of two large",
                "area multiwire proportional counters, each having an",
                "active area of 27.9 x 35.7 cm**2 and giving an",
                "angular coverage in-plane of 75 degree.",
                "   MWPC 1: angular coverage of theta1 = 95-170 degree",
                "           for 40Ca + 124Sn, theta1 = 55-130 degree",
                "   MWPC 2: angular coverage of theta2 = 5-80 degree"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two silicon surface barrier detectors were",
                "placed out of plane, at thetamon = 23 degree and",
                "phi1 = 90 degree, phi2 = 270 degree to detect the",
                "elastically scattered beam particles that were used",
                "for normalization. The solid angle of the detection",
                "system was determined by using 28Si+197Au and",
                "40Ca+197Au elastic scattering."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The emission angle of the detected fission",
                "fragments and their velocities."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two MWPCs for the detection of binary fission",
                "fragments in coincidence."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross sections were converted from the lab frame",
                "to the CM frame assuming binary fission and by taking",
                "the average kinetic energy of the fragments given by",
                "the Viola systematics."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Fission yields corresponding to 5 degree bins in angle",
                "were extracted and were corrected for the detector",
                "solid angle to get the differential cross sections for",
                "each energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
